snippet.textDisplay: This video is exactly why Disney needs to release unspecialized versions of the original trilogy. Some amazing men and women pioneered groundbreaking special effects and worked tirelessly to make some amazing movies. Their hard work needs to be preserved for all the world to see. Yes it has tons of flaws based on todays standards, but for the late seventies and early eighties these effects were extraordinary. Shame on George Lucas for trying to wipe away from the permanent record all their hard work.
